This paper is primarily focused on the communication aspect of V2V networks, which falls under the category of computer networks and communications (cs.NI). The use of reinforcement learning (RL) algorithms to optimize the resource allocation process is a key aspect of the paper, which suggests that it could also be classified under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of a centralized scheduler, which involves coordination and control of multiple agents, making it relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) category. Finally, the paper deals with the allocation of resources, which is a key aspect of information theory (cs.IT).
